    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Nov. 5./80</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I am so much engaged I cannot write at length; but if you will consult my “Descent of Man” p. 590, 591. Ch. XX (in one of the later editions) you will find all that I know about their marriage arrangements, with some references.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> If you will look to index, under monkeys, you will find somewhat on their mental &amp; moral nature.—</p>
                    <p>Heartily wishing you all success | I remain, dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway… S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n2">1.2 Ch. XX] <hi rend="italic">interl</hi> </note>
                <note xml:id="tnote.n3">1.3 will] <hi rend="italic">added</hi> </note>
            </div>
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The letter to which this is a reply has not been found. In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1967.xml"><hi rend="italic">Descent</hi> 2d ed.</ref>, pp. 590–1, CD discussed marriage practices among ‘savages’ and monogamy and polygamy among primates. He referred principally to the work of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3401.xml">Lewis Henry Morgan</ref>, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3277.xml">John Ferguson McLennan</ref>, and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_3026.xml">John Lubbock</ref>.</note>
            
        </div>
    
